                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32n5040v/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>in <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> and in which I expressed my\n                                        views<lb/> on the apathy of our people in pretty strong\n                                        language<lb/> This sermon is written in German and was<lb/>\n                                        thought so pertinent to the <del>subject</del>\n                                        school-project, that <persName>Mr<lb/> Mack</persName> asked\n                                        it of me and had it circulated<lb/> among his friends for\n                                        digestion. But I would<lb/> not take the trouble to\n                                        translate it, nor tax<lb/> you with it. I thought it\n                                        indelicate on my<lb/> part, to give the subject the\n                                        slightest notice<lb/> I thought, however, God save me of my\n                                        friends<lb/> all.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am just in receipt of a letter from<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr. De Sola</persName>,\n                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName>, advising me of\n                                        his<lb/> intention of publishing Beth<add>?</add>\n                                        English's<lb/> work, for circulation among the Jews<lb/>\n                                        only. The work is out of print, and its<lb/> republication\n                                        can only be of benefit.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">May God guide your counsels, and<lb/> bless you\n                                        with long life and happiness.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">James K. Gutheim</persName>\n                              </p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32n5040v/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
